<br>
I would be interested if you could re-examine your data with an eye towards what mobs fit that pattern from which expansion. All of the mobs that you named in your post were from the old world,I would be interested to see what happens in Kunark and then Velious and Luclin.<br>
<br>
----<br>
<br>
Ceum writes:<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I'd like to point out that an NPC's &quot;misses&quot; are actually hits for zero (or less), which actually reinforces the modal damage- and DI arguments.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I'd like to pint out that again that this has no basis yet. I just need one person to demonstrate or prove this please. Otherwise stop saying that &quot;HITs can be mitigated to MISSes&quot; and say &quot;It is a possible hypothetical that HITs could be mitigated to MISSes&quot;.<br>
<br>
I am not saying that this does or does not happen, I am open to it being proven or demonstrated. But people saying that it is the way it works makes me think I missed when VI stated this to us or someone provided a proof. Prove it or let it go guys.<br>
<br>
----<br>
<br>
Fendryl, this is the only time someone has stated that mob hits don't completely follow the formula of DB + (x * DI). Serioulsy if this is the case please provide us with us much data as you have, we really need to look at this in depth. CT is a newly revamped zone and it is possible they did something new there that we should be factoring in.<br>
<br>
Please, gather data and post as much of it as you can. Same goes for anyone else reading this, go get data off mobs in CT.<br>
<br>
If it's an error by Fendryl I would rather find out quickly and reinstate the formula as complete. If it's not an error then we have a situation where VI can modify MIN hits only (which is bizarre).<br>
<br>
